HEADWORD: Paleontology
<hw>Pa`le*on*tol"o*gy</hw>
<pr>(p⟦amac⟧`l⟦esl⟧*⟦ocr⟧n*t⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Paleo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>'o`nta</grk> existing things +
<ets>-logy</ets>. Cf. <er>Ontology</er>.]</ety> <def>The science which
treats of the ancient life of the earth, or of fossils which are the
remains of such life.</def>⟦br⟧
